ver, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Walton, Leicestershire, England":"Walton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Walton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places called Walton, which are named with Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Briton, serf’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>), <i>wald</i> ‘woodland’, <i>wall</i> ‘wall’, or <i>wælla</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","History: George Walton (1741–1804) signed the Declaration of Independence. He was born in Prince Edward County, VA, whither his grandfather had emigrated from England in 1682. He moved to Savannah, GA, and became governor of GA and a prominent jurist."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Walton was born in 1216, in Walton, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William de Walton, was 27 and his mother, Elizabeth Hance, was 22. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs Thomas Walton. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1216–":"1216–Surnud","1190–1287":"1190–1287","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1216–Male":"1216–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1246–1306":"1246–1306","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1195–1255":"1195–1255","1190":"1190","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1246":"1246","1255":"1255","1287":"1287","about 1246":"umbes 1246","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","1250":"1250","1306":"1306","Over Walton Manor, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walton, Leicestershire, England":"Walton, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1216–":"1216–Kuollut","1190–1287":"1190–1287","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1216–Male":"1216–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1246–1306":"1246–1306","1190–1250":"1190–1250","1195–1255":"1195–1255","1190":"1190","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1246":"1246","1255":"1255","1287":"1287","about 1246":"noin 1246","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","1250":"1250","1306":"1306","Over Walton Manor, Cheshire, England":"Over, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Steeple Bumpstead, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walton, Leicestershire, England":"Walton, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1216–":"1216–Décédé","1190–1287":"1190–1287","1215–Female":"1215–Dé